title: How does breast cancer screening coverage compare to other countries?
analysis_commentary: Breast cancer screening coverage of females aged 50-69 in the UK has been steady over the years with an average of 76%. While the UK outperforms many OECD countries, screening rates in the Netherlands, United States and Finland are still higher.
data_source: Organisation for Economic Co-operation and Development, Health Data
